le in the production of contemporary film and television.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCinematographyxSpecial effectsxHistory. 0aZoom lens photography. 0aZoom lensesxHistory. 0aZoom lenses. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  aAlfred Hitchcock.  aAmerican.  aMichael Snow.  aVertigo.  aWavelength.  afilm.  atelevision.  azoom lens.  azoom.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311066608340uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/9780813587233zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813587233423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813587233.jpg  a978-3-11-066608-3  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK